    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix missed scheduling opportunity due to unconditional debug call in EPS update type encoding\n\n### Summary\nA missed scheduling opportunity occurs when UEs with pending data are not scheduled properly downstream of the `dump_eps_update_type_xml` function. Investigation revealed that the `encode_u8_eps_update_type` function was calling `dump_eps_update_type_xml` unconditionally, even when NAS debugging was disabled. This unnecessary function call could interfere with timing-sensitive scheduling operations.\n\nThe root cause was an inconsistency where one call to `dump_eps_update_type_xml` was not wrapped in the `#if defined (NAS_DEBUG)` conditional like all other calls in the same file. This has been fixed by adding the proper conditional compilation wrapper.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair3/NAS/COMMON/IES/EpsUpdateType.c`: Added `#if defined (NAS_DEBUG)` conditional wrapper around `dump_eps_update_type_xml` call in `encode_u8_eps_update_type` function to match the pattern used in other functions in the same file.\n\n"
}